TITLE: Complete Post Model Example in ZModel
DESCRIPTION: Example showing a Post model with various field types including ID, timestamps, primitive types, optional fields, arrays and relations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zenstackhq/zenstack-docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-1.x/reference/zmodel-language.md#2025-04-10_snippet_46

LANGUAGE: zmodel
CODE:
```
model Post {
    // "id" field is a mandatory unique identifier of this model
    id String @id @default(uuid())

    // fields can be DateTime
    createdAt DateTime @default(now())
    updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt

    // or string
    title String

    // or integer
    viewCount Int @default(0)

    // and optional
    content String?

    // and a list too
    tags String[]

    // and can reference another model too
    comments Comment[]
}
```

