TITLE: Simple Post Model with Access Policies in ZModel
DESCRIPTION: A complete example of a Post model with access policies that reject operations for unauthenticated users, allow operations for owners, and permit public reading of posts.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zenstackhq/zenstack-docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-1.x/reference/zmodel-language.md#2025-04-10_snippet_57

LANGUAGE: zmodel
CODE:
```
model Post {
    // reject all operations if user's not logged in
    @@deny('all', auth() == null)

    // allow all operations if the entity's owner matches the current user
    @@allow('all', auth() == owner)

    // posts are readable to anyone
    @allow('read', true)
}
```

