TITLE: Implementing Parent-Child Access Policies with Duplicated Logic in ZenStack
DESCRIPTION: A ZModel schema for a Todo application with duplicated access control policies between List and Todo models. The List owner has full access while public lists can be read by anyone. Todo items inherit the same permissions as their parent List.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zenstackhq/zenstack-docs/blob/main/blog/check-function/index.md#2025-04-10_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: zmodel
CODE:
```
model List {
  id       Int @id
  name     String
  public   Boolean
  author   User @relation(fields: [authorId], references: [id])
  authorId Int
  todos    Todo[]

  // highlight-start
  @@allow('all', auth() == author)
  @@allow('read', public)
  // highlight-end
}

model Todo {
  id     Int @id
  name   String
  list   List @relation(fields: [listId], references: [id])
  listId Int

  // highlight-start
  @@allow('all', auth() == list.author)
  @@allow('read', list.public)
  // highlight-end
}
```

