TITLE: Creating Enhanced PrismaClient Helper for Current User in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: A helper function that retrieves the current user's information from Clerk authentication and creates an enhanced PrismaClient with proper user context for access control enforcement. This allows database queries to automatically filter results based on user permissions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zenstackhq/zenstack-docs/blob/main/blog/clerk-multitenancy/index.mdx#2025-04-10_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { Role } from "@prisma/client";
import { enhance } from "@zenstackhq/runtime";

export async function getUserDb() {
  // get the current user's information from Clerk
  const { userId, orgId, orgRole } = await auth();

  // create an enhanced Prisma Client with proper user context
  const user = userId
    ? {
        userId,
        currentOrgId: orgId,
        currentOrgRole: orgRole
      }
    : undefined; // anonymous
  return enhance(prisma, { user });
}
```

