TITLE: Implementing Row Level Security in PostgreSQL for Blog Posts
DESCRIPTION: SQL code demonstrating how to set up Row Level Security (RLS) policies in Supabase for controlling access to blog posts. Shows policies for owner access and public read access to published posts.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zenstackhq/zenstack-docs/blob/main/blog/supabase.mdx#2025-04-10_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
# Simple RLS for blog posts

# owner has full access to her own posts
CREATE POLICY post_owner_policy ON post
    USING (owner = current_user);

# all users can read published posts
CREATE POLICY post_read_policy ON post FOR SELECT
    USING (published = true);
```

