TITLE: Creating Database Trigger for User Synchronization in SQL
DESCRIPTION: SQL code to create a function and trigger for synchronizing new users from Supabase Auth to the public User table. This ensures that the User table stays in sync with Supabase Auth.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zenstackhq/zenstack-docs/blob/main/docs/guides/authentication/supabase.md#2025-04-10_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
-- inserts a row into public."User"
create function public.handle_new_user()
returns trigger
language plpgsql
security definer set search_path = public
as $$
begin
  insert into public."User" (id)
  values (new.id);
  return new;
end;
$$;

-- trigger the function every time a user is created
create trigger on_auth_user_created
  after insert on auth.users
  for each row execute procedure public.handle_new_user();
```

