TITLE: Implementing Row-Level Security with PostgreSQL
DESCRIPTION: This SQL example demonstrates how to implement row-level security in PostgreSQL by creating a chat table with policies that restrict access based on the current user. The policy ensures users can only see chats where they're the sender or receiver and can only insert messages as themselves.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zenstackhq/zenstack-docs/blob/main/blog/secure-api/index.md#2025-04-10_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
