TITLE: Creating SQL Triggers for Syncing Supabase Auth with Custom User Model
DESCRIPTION: SQL database trigger setup that automatically synchronizes new users from Supabase Auth's auth.users table to the public.User table. This ensures user data consistency without directly coupling with Supabase's internal schemas.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zenstackhq/zenstack-docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-1.x/guides/authentication/supabase.md#2025-04-10_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
-- inserts a row into public."User"
create function public.handle_new_user()
returns trigger
language plpgsql
security definer set search_path = public
as $$
begin
  insert into public."User" (id)
  values (new.id);
  return new;
end;
$$;

-- trigger the function every time a user is created
create trigger on_auth_user_created
  after insert on auth.users
  for each row execute procedure public.handle_new_user();
```

