TITLE: Configuring PostgreSQL Row-Level Security Policies
DESCRIPTION: SQL statements that create row-level security policies for articles in PostgreSQL, enabling fine-grained access control based on user and group permissions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zenstackhq/zenstack-docs/blob/main/blog/how-to-authz/index.md#2025-04-10_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
CREATE POLICY user_access_policy ON Article
FOR SELECT
USING (
  EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM AccessControlList
    WHERE 
      AccessControlList.resource_id = Article.id AND
      AccessControlList.user_id = current_user AND
      AccessControlList.permission_type = 'read'
  )
);

CREATE POLICY group_access_policy ON Article
FOR SELECT
USING (
  EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM AccessControlList
    JOIN user_groups ON AccessControlList.group_id = user_groups.group_id
    WHERE 
      AccessControlList.resource_id = Article.id AND
      user_groups.user_id = current_user AND
      AccessControlList.permission_type = 'read'
  )
);
```

