TITLE: Optimized findManyAndCount with Special Case Handling in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: An optimized implementation of findManyAndCount for Prisma that avoids the second count query when the number of items returned is less than the requested limit, saving database resources.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zenstackhq/zenstack-docs/blob/main/blog/trade-off/index.md#2025-04-10_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
const { items, count } = await prisma.$transaction(async (tx) => {
    const items = await tx.user.findMany(query);

    // If it is true, we could avoid another query
    if (query.take && items.length < query.take) {
        return { items, count: items.length };
    }
    const count = await tx.user.count({ where: query.where });
    return { items, count };
});
```

