TITLE: Accessing *-to-one Relations in ZenStack Policy Rules
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to access *-to-one relations in ZenStack policy rules using dot notation. It shows a policy rule that allows updating a Todo if its related List is not private.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zenstackhq/zenstack-docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-1.x/the-complete-guide/part1/4-access-policy/4.4-relations.md#2025-04-10_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: zmodel
CODE:
```
model List {
    id Int
    private Boolean
}

model Todo {
    id Int
    list List @relation(...)

    // `list` references a to-one relation
    @@allow('update', !list.private)
}
```

