TITLE: Revoking Supabase Anonymous Access Privileges
DESCRIPTION: This SQL snippet shows how to revoke all privileges from the 'anon' role to prevent unauthenticated access to the Supabase database. It includes revoking current privileges and altering default privileges for future objects in the public schema.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zenstackhq/zenstack-docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-1.x/guides/supabase-security.md#2025-04-10_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
-- Revoke current privileges
REVOKE SELECT ON ALL TABLES IN SCHEMA public FROM anon;
REVOKE USAGE ON ALL SEQUENCES IN SCHEMA public FROM anon;
REVOKE EXECUTE ON ALL FUNCTIONS IN SCHEMA public FROM anon;

-- Revoke default privileges for future objects
ALTER DEFAULT PRIVILEGES IN SCHEMA public REVOKE ALL ON TABLES FROM anon;
ALTER DEFAULT PRIVILEGES IN SCHEMA public REVOKE ALL ON FUNCTIONS FROM anon;
ALTER DEFAULT PRIVILEGES IN SCHEMA public REVOKE ALL ON SEQUENCES FROM anon;
```

